    <body>
        
        <div type="letter">
            <div type="text">
                <opener>
                    <placeName><hi rend="print">Down, | Beckenham, Kent.</hi> | (<hi rend="print">Railway Station | Orpington. S.E.R.</hi>)</placeName>
                    <salute>My dear Sir</salute>
                </opener>
                <div type="transcription">
                     
<p>Very many thanks for your clear &amp; full letter, which has been a great relief to my mind, for I feared that I might have blundered in some incomprehensible manner.<ref target="#foot.f2"/></p>
<p>Yours sincerely | Charles Darwin</p> 
                </div>
            </div>
            <div type="tnotes">
                <note xml:id="tnote.n1">0.1 (<hi rend="italic">Railway … S.E.R.</hi>)] <hi rend="italic">parentheses added</hi> </note>
            </div>
            
            
            
            
            
            
        </div>
        
        
        <div type="footnotes">
            <note xml:id="foot.f1">The date is conjectured from a note in an unknown hand.</note>
            <note xml:id="foot.f2">The letter has not been found, but see the <ref target="./DCP-LETT-13402.xml">letter from Hugo de Vries, 15 October 1881</ref>. In that letter, De Vries mentioned that he was going to repeat some of CD’s observations on worms. The missing letter may have discussed these observations. </note>    
        </div>   
       
